WEBVTT



00:00:00.224 --> 00:00:03.392
Well, conclave begins today, and as we hear these readings today,

00:00:03.136 --> 00:00:07.360
From the epistle to the Hebrews in the Gospel of John, I'm flooded with memories.

00:00:07.520 --> 00:00:17.568
Ah, Hebrews is a great meditation on priesthood, and when I began studying Latin, I found that there are a lot of words for priests, and one of them is Pontifect.

00:00:17.088 --> 00:00:18.048
effects.

00:00:17.984 --> 00:00:20.000
The bridge builder,

00:00:19.680 --> 00:00:24.288
And the Pope is the Pontifex Maximus, the great

00:00:24.224 --> 00:00:27.488
Bridge builder, the the greatest bridge builder.

00:00:27.424 --> 00:00:28.672
And I had

00:00:29.568 --> 00:00:39.616
I don't want to say own vision, but a clarity about the role of the Pontifex. I was offering Mass one time at a church, and at the high altar they had a beautiful tabernacle.

00:00:39.136 --> 00:00:48.064
Knackle and I went to the tabernacle to get a suborium and I opened the door and I genuinely like as I stood up, I looked and I saw that the back wall.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.208
Of the tabernacle.

00:00:49.952 --> 00:00:54.272
Was gold polished to a mirror finish.

00:00:54.432 --> 00:00:59.488
So as I looked ahead, I saw not only our Lord, but behind me.

00:00:59.328 --> 00:01:00.928
His people,

00:01:01.312 --> 00:01:02.912
And somehow

00:01:02.848 --> 00:01:05.792
The sky from Newark, New Jersey.

00:01:05.728 --> 00:01:08.512
Was carrying the needs

00:01:08.352 --> 00:01:10.112
And the offerings

00:01:09.984 --> 00:01:18.656
Of God's people to God, and returning from the tabernacle, the dwelling place of God.

00:01:18.560 --> 00:01:22.560
The benefits of God for God's holy people

00:01:22.848 --> 00:01:32.896
What is an astonishing thing to happen to a man from New Jersey, but it happened and I'm here to witness to that and that's just a very small thing.

00:01:32.416 --> 00:01:33.216
thing.

00:01:33.056 --> 00:01:38.048
Magnify beyond our comprehension when we think of the office.

00:01:37.856 --> 00:01:39.392
of the Pope

00:01:39.872 --> 00:01:48.352
And as I meditate on priesthood, I can't help but think of my experience as a faculty member in seminaries.

00:01:48.544 --> 00:01:52.608
And the most burdensome part of the task was the voting.

00:01:52.576 --> 00:01:57.056
Do we let this man into the seminary or not, or do we delay him?

00:01:57.024 --> 00:02:06.784
Once he's in, do we keep him? Do we give him a time out? Do we dismiss him? And when he applies for ordination, do we say yes, wait.

00:02:06.752 --> 00:02:09.056
No goodbye

00:02:08.832 --> 00:02:10.976
And I was always in

00:02:10.816 --> 00:02:12.160
English.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:13.280
Over that over that

00:02:13.152 --> 00:02:14.624
Because,

00:02:15.008 --> 00:02:17.312
I'm making a tremendous

00:02:17.152 --> 00:02:19.360
Decision for the church.

00:02:19.520 --> 00:02:22.336
That once made, we can't take it.

00:02:22.080 --> 00:02:26.432
Back, we can't say never mind or oops or do over.

00:02:26.848 --> 00:02:29.760
And one time, only one time mercifully,

00:02:29.536 --> 00:02:39.584
If you've been to an ordination, you present the candidate for ordination. Usually it's the seminary rector who says to the bishop, we recommend these men or brothers to ordination to the rank of deacon.

00:02:39.104 --> 00:02:40.896
The deacon, the rank of priest.

00:02:40.736 --> 00:02:45.312
And the bishop asks, Do you find these men to be worthy? Well,

00:02:45.056 --> 00:02:48.896
I had to present a candidate for the acinet to the bishop.

00:02:49.696 --> 00:02:57.856
And he looked at me and said, Do you find these men to be worthy? And happily I had my script, having inquired among the people of God and those responding.

00:02:57.568 --> 00:03:00.704
Then finally you get to, "I testify."

00:03:01.184 --> 00:03:08.832
that this man is worthy and my knees were knocking. I said, "I don't like this. I don't like this kind of..."

00:03:08.864 --> 00:03:13.792
responsibility. There's too much human judgment involved.

00:03:13.536 --> 00:03:14.752
Too much.

00:03:15.072 --> 00:03:18.336
There's more art than there is science and

00:03:18.432 --> 00:03:23.168
You got to rely on the Holy Spirit. And oh, I don't like that because, you know,

00:03:23.008 --> 00:03:25.696
He doesn't follow my tune.

00:03:26.464 --> 00:03:27.392
Well,

00:03:27.584 --> 00:03:29.536
So now let's imagine

00:03:29.312 --> 00:03:31.328
These poor souls,

00:03:31.136 --> 00:03:33.984
Walking into the Sistine Chapel,

00:03:34.848 --> 00:03:38.080
And as they approach with a valid in hand,

00:03:37.856 --> 00:03:41.632
They are walking towards Michelangelo's final judgment.

00:03:41.664 --> 00:03:46.176
And before he drops his ballot in, he says this.

00:03:45.920 --> 00:03:50.112
I call as my witness Christ the Lord.

00:03:49.952 --> 00:03:52.608
Who will be my judge?

00:03:52.640 --> 00:03:55.616
That my vote is given to the one who

00:03:55.392 --> 00:03:57.376
Who before God?

00:03:57.184 --> 00:03:58.464
I think,

00:03:58.240 --> 00:03:59.552
Should be,

00:03:59.392 --> 00:04:00.640
elected.

00:04:00.448 --> 00:04:04.224
I think I would faint halfway through that formula.

00:04:04.448 --> 00:04:08.736
So our Lord tells us to love one another.

00:04:09.024 --> 00:04:10.624
And surely,

00:04:10.400 --> 00:04:12.512
To obey his commandments,

00:04:12.448 --> 00:04:20.160
And I think somewhere in there, maybe even if it's just in the emanations of the penumbra of his commandments, to borrow a phrase,

00:04:20.096 --> 00:04:25.120
Ah, part of what it means to be a disciple is to do what's best for his bride.

00:04:25.664 --> 00:04:27.616
That has to be.

00:04:27.648 --> 00:04:30.752
Part of what you can is commanded.

00:04:31.040 --> 00:04:40.032
So I think it's an act of justice. It might be a matter of enlightened self-interest and surely it is a work of charity.

00:04:40.064 --> 00:04:46.112
To intercede for those poor men who will exercise the terrible burden,

00:04:45.984 --> 00:04:49.600
Of casting ballots for the Pope.

00:04:51.200 --> 00:04:52.640
I wouldn't

00:04:52.480 --> 00:04:56.224
I wouldn't want it. I don't have the character to do that.

00:04:57.152 --> 00:04:58.912
And this is where

00:04:58.720 --> 00:05:02.240
Grace and nature must meet.

00:05:02.240 --> 00:05:10.944
This is where the Holy Spirit has to break through perception and cognition and bring light.

00:05:10.848 --> 00:05:15.072
To mind and heart as never before.

00:05:16.224 --> 00:05:24.448
And we all know well enough for those who dare to cooperate with grace at such a level, unexpected and amazing,

00:05:24.288 --> 00:05:25.344
Things

00:05:25.152 --> 00:05:26.272
Happen?

00:05:26.784 --> 00:05:31.488
So let's pray in these days for the gift of

00:05:31.264 --> 00:05:33.184
Many miracles.

00:05:33.888 --> 00:05:36.640
In the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit.
